DrProtectionGroup create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed and resume through
status.async.current as the canonical in-flight
tracker.
List responses expose DrProtectionGroupSummary
items only, so the runtime rereads
GetDrProtectionGroup for authoritative
logLocation and members projection instead of
treating summaries as complete observed state.
The published runtime keeps role,
lifecycleState, lifecycleSubState, peer fields,
and polymorphic members truthful in status while
limiting in-place writes to
UpdateDrProtectionGroupDetails.
Associate/Disassociate role changes, compartment
moves, DR plans, and the broader member-action
families remain out of scope for this first
controller-backed disasterrecovery rollout.
end note
